PROMISE CODE lacked a needed rally after establishing an inside stance mid pack and saving ground around the bend. ABES DAY showed reserve from the start, trailed the field through the bend, and passed a tiring rival in late strides. NIGHT VISION was unhurried from outset, chased frontrunners around the turn from a two path stance, then could not run down leaders in final furlong.

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 21, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since July 21, 2023 Allowed 4 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming, Starter, Or State Bred Races Not Considered In Allowances). (If management deems it necessary to take this race off the Turf, it will be run at a distance of 1 Mile on the main track.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WILD EXPRESS rushed from outset, gained first command, established a ground saving stance, and led every step of way for a gate to wire score. MY GIRL MELLY tucked to the rail shortly after the start to save ground around the first turn, angled out to be widest of all at upper stretch, was gaining on the leader in the final furlong, but was forced to check at the sixteenth pole to avoid a fallen rider. COURTNEY FAY finished evenly after being unhurried in the early stages and swinging to five wide at upper stretch. ROLLIN BLACKOUT showed patience from the start and tucked to save ground, then improved placing with a mild rally. GET SERIOUS pressed the early pace from a four wide pose, was within striking distance at upper stretch while four wide, but was forced to alter path at the sixteenth pole to avoid a fallen rider. BASKET CASE came up empty and failed to produce a late kick after settling into the second flight and trekking four wide at upper stretch. HIGHWAY SIXTY ONE failed to threaten and passed tiring rivals after rating back through the opening half. CHILLAXIFICATION rushed from outset to force the pacesetter through the opening half before fading rapidly in the homestretch. DOWNTOWN ABBY lacked a needed rally after showing reserve from outset. OUTLINING settled into second flight shortly after the start, trekked the inside, rated on the heels of the leader at upper stretch, was under a stiff drive, then lost rider at the sixteenth pole. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.
